ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for post-traumatic stress symptoms at timepoint calculated in all individuals using PTSD Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals.
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for post-traumatic stress symptoms at timepoint calculated in whites alone using PTSD Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals.
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for post-traumatic stress symptoms at timepoint calculated in blacks alone using PTSD Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from black individuals.
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for depressive symptoms at timepoint calculated in all individuals using depression Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals.
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for depressive symptoms at timepoint calculated in whites alone using depression Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals.
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for depressive symptoms at timepoint calculated in blacks alone using depression Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals (depression GWAS did not have GWAS data from black individuals).
Notes: Higher PRS indicates higher genetic risk for developing symptoms

ElementDescription: Standardized Polygenic Risk Score (PRS) for post-traumatic stress symptoms at timepoint calculated in all individuals using PTSD Genome Wide Association Study (GWAS) data from white individuals (mean = 0, standard deviation (SD) = 1).
